## 2026-04-04 - UI fetch hooks have inconsistent abort/timeout patterns
- Extracted `createFetchSignal(disconnectSignal?, timeoutMs?)` factory to `apiFetch.ts`. Combines `AbortSignal.timeout(timeoutMs)` with an optional disconnect/controller signal via `AbortSignal.any`. Default timeout 5 s; callers can override (e.g. 10 s for batch writes).
- `useGeneratorPreview.ts`: wrapped both the preview POST and the existing-tokens GET with `createFetchSignal(controller.signal)` — previously had no timeout (could hang indefinitely).
- `useResolvers.ts`: added `createFetchSignal()` to `fetchResolvers` (previously no signal at all); added `createFetchSignal(controller.signal)` to the resolve-tokens POST.

